<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,232,418]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Most authors (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hull" box="[409,545,232,258]" pageId="4" pageNumber="18" refString="Hull, F. M. (1949 a) The morphology and inter-relationship of the genera of syrphid flies, recent and fossil. Transaction of the Zoological Society, London, 26, 157 - 408. [1949.05. ??]" type="journal article" year="1949" yearSuffix="a">
Hull 
<number box="[469,531,232,258]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1949.0">1949</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[557,603,232,258]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="332.0">332</number>
) have overlooked Macquart's designation of 
<taxonomicName box="[1134,1227,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Plesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[1134,1227,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[1311,1362,232,258]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
of his genus, and have used the name 
<taxonomicName box="[522,595,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Plesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[522,595,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Plesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as if based on the other included species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart." authorityName="Macquart." box="[1090,1283,272,298]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Plesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anale">
<emphasis box="[1090,1155,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">anale</emphasis>
Macquart.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[1290,1436,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Plesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anale">
<emphasis box="[1290,1436,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Plesia anale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName box="[296,454,312,337]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Chrysogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[296,454,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Chrysogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[596,724,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Eristalinae">Eristalinae</taxonomicName>
, tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[798,945,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Brachyopini">Brachyopini</taxonomicName>
) and will be designated the 
<typeStatus box="[1276,1327,312,338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
of a new genus. Fortunately, the name 
<taxonomicName box="[509,583,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Plesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[509,583,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Plesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is preoccupied and, therefore, will not supplant the well-known name 
<taxonomicName box="[151,310,392,417]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,310,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Melanostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
